shuffling_registration_height_help: Shuffling won't start unless the required number of participants register before this height.
phasing_duration_help: Restricts the phasing period of the transactions issued by the account. Useful in case the controlled account is compromised. The maximum duration determines for how long an attacker will be able to lock the account funds before the controlling entities are able to rescue them to a new account. The minimum duration, together with the Maximum Pending Fees, determines at what rate an attacker will be able to burn through fees the NXT owned by the controlled account
maximum_pending_fees_help: Maximum sum of the pending transactions fees. Divide this by the minimum phasing duration, and you will get the amount of NXT that can be spent in fees by the controlled account per block
error_fee_exceeds_max_account_control_fe: Maximum total fees limit of __maxFee__ NXT exceeded

shuffling_node_running_warning: After creating or joining a shuffling, you must keep your node online and your shuffler running, leaving enough funds in your account to cover the 12 NXT shuffling fees, until the shuffling completes! If you don't and miss your turn, you will be charged 1000 NXT.

publish_offer_help: An exchange offer models real world exchange booth, offering to exchange currencies at different buy/sell rates and limits. If you only want to buy, or only to sell, leave the opposite limits at 0, and enter the same buy and sell rates
